		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>HGL stresses me out.</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>This game is one of the most fun I've ever played, and definitely the most fun game that I'm currently playing.<br />
<br />
But I'm still not happy and comfortable with a single one of my characters.  I've already re-rolled one of them since guild invites went out, and I seriously think I'm going to re-roll the rest.<br />
<br />
Permanent skill points and attribute points make me go batty.  I'm just so afraid of screwing a character up that I constantly go &quot;oh shit, I'm not going to like that later&quot; and re-roll.<br />
<br />
At this point I think I'm just going to pick one class (leaning toward engineer), figure out a skill and attribute plan I'm decently comfortable with, and take it through the game for better or worse.<br />
<br />
We'll see if that plan actually stands up.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
