		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>There are tons of ways to play the game though, so there really isn't a right or wrong. I remember a post from one of the devs and he said Bill Roper plays a Guardian differently than he does and he is the one who basically created the class. Roper jumps in the middle and uses a lot of stuns. The dev uses the grappler and pulls in mobs one at a time. <br />
<br />
On my evoker, he is going to be a jack of all trades, master of none. I have taken a lot of different abilities so I can be prepared in any situation. That is just my play style though. Others will be heavily focused in one or two areas. It's all a matter of personal preference. If I find something that I really don't like, then I roll up another one and make the changes. It really doesn't take that long to level up. It gets even faster as you learn more of the nuances of the game. <br />
<br />
I am having hella fun in the game though. <br />
<br />
Last night I was a sad sad man though. I bought a mask off a vendor because I thought it looked cool and am wearing it now. My old one was a little better, but didn't look as good.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
